This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for head pose estimation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on improving the accuracy of the existing methods, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of loss functions and bounding box margin adjustment also indicates that it may belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
